<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> off one’s own bat • off the bat</xh5><p> <i>off one’s own bat</i>—(coll.) 1. by one’s own efforts: I felt that I’d like to get some money <u>off my own bat</u>. 2. on one’s own initiative: Don’t think I’m being nosey, but you never tell me anything <u>off your own bat</u>.</p><p><i>off the bat</i>—(coll.) on the spot; right away: McGowan was also striving to catch the bright smiles tossed about by Rosy. He picked them <u>off the bat</u>.</p> </entry>
